<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871009-0089 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News:Disc Technology NamesKareiva Chief, President</HL><DD> 10/09/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> DSTC WNEWS </IN><DATELINE> BILLERICA, Mass.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Disc Technology Corp. named Patrick H. Kareiva chief executive officer, president and a director of the maker of hard disks for computers.    Mr. Kareiva, 43 years old, was most recently president of Lowell, Mass.-based LISP Machines Inc. As chief executive of Disc Technology, he succeeds Donald D. Bruck, 51, who resigned from that post and the position of chairman. Mr. Bruck will continue as a consultant to the company.    As president and director, Mr. Kareiva succeeds Ronald D. Weiss, who had served as acting president since May. Mr. Weiss will continue his responsibilities as vice president, engineering.    The company said Leonard E. Smollen and Richard A. Charpie both resigned as directors. The position of chairman is currently unfilled. </TEXT></DOC>